You're free to do that in your own code, but I would recommend against it.  If you do that, your code will break if you want to switch optimizers.  If you really do want to replace one character with a whole function, I'd recommend:

```
def maximize(optimizer, value, ...):
  return optimizer.minimize(-value, ...)
```
